34:47.752 --> 34:49.150
# You know it's gonna be #

34:49.187 --> 34:50.710
# The ace of spades #

34:50.755 --> 34:52.813
# The ace of spades #

35:12.810 --> 35:15.244
My god, do we really suck...

35:15.279 --> 35:17.509
or is this guy really that good?

35:17.548 --> 35:19.140
Come on, boys!

35:19.183 --> 35:21.083
He ain't out of the briar patch yet!

35:40.138 --> 35:42.003
Shoot the dog, shoot the dog.

35:42.039 --> 35:43.301
No.

35:44.742 --> 35:46.767
- Why not?
- I like dogs.

36:08.266 --> 36:09.995
Wait a minute.

36:12.904 --> 36:15.805
Oh, that rat bastard.

36:31.122 --> 36:32.248
What is it?

36:32.924 --> 36:34.289
It's the baby's diaper.

36:39.297 --> 36:41.697
This idea blows, Smith.

36:41.732 --> 36:43.222
It's the only idea we got.

36:43.267 --> 36:45.758
You actually think
that Oliver's mother...

36:45.803 --> 36:47.896
lived near a heavy metal club...

36:47.939 --> 36:51.375
...and that he could hear the music
while he was still inside the womb?

36:51.409 --> 36:52.808
Yep. That's why he doesn't cry...

36:52.843 --> 36:54.708
when he's listenin' to some
headbanger's bash.

36:54.745 --> 36:56.042
Ridiculous.

36:56.714 --> 36:58.079
Well, he isn't cryin' now.

37:01.719 --> 37:05.382
So this is the only club near where
I encountered the baby's mother.

37:05.423 --> 37:07.891
I still say this is a wild hunch.

37:07.925 --> 37:10.257
Yeah? So how do you explain
all these boxes of diapers?

37:10.294 --> 37:12.159
Somebody's been stocking up.

37:12.196 --> 37:13.959
Let's find out who.

37:16.133 --> 37:19.296
# You sear my legs,
song birds cheer #

37:19.337 --> 37:21.237
# Eat my neck #

37:21.272 --> 37:23.240
# I can't,
I can't let it go grey #

37:23.274 --> 37:26.175
# I can't break, I can't break #

37:26.210 --> 37:31.170
# I can't break,
I can't break, I can't break #

37:31.215 --> 37:34.082
- You the owner of this place?
- Who's askin'?

37:34.118 --> 37:35.676
I am.

37:37.888 --> 37:40.322
- Can I buy you a drink?
- No.

37:42.860 --> 37:45.124
Just as I suspected.

37:45.162 --> 37:47.562
He really is into jewelry.

37:51.135 --> 37:52.659
Who occupies the room upstairs?

37:52.703 --> 37:54.102
go to hell.

37:54.138 --> 37:55.628
Don't mess with me.

37:55.673 --> 37:57.504
You ain't got the <i>cojones.</i>

38:00.278 --> 38:01.802
Oh, god.

38:03.381 --> 38:05.212
So who were these guys?

38:05.249 --> 38:09.151
I rented the place to some suit
11 months ago.

38:09.186 --> 38:11.711
He paid the whole year in cash.

38:11.756 --> 38:13.223
I never saw him again.

38:13.257 --> 38:15.623
I just figured they were
usin' the back way.

38:21.899 --> 38:23.594
Beat it.

38:38.949 --> 38:40.348
<i>Oh, madonna.</i>

38:41.752 --> 38:42.844
<i>Che orrore!</i>

38:43.487 --> 38:45.352
This is pretty fucked up.

39:15.319 --> 39:17.480
Sir, it's your go-to guy.

39:18.189 --> 39:20.054
All the mothers have been killed.

39:20.091 --> 39:22.525
Only one escaped, temporarily.

39:22.560 --> 39:25.996
We found her body and confirmed
that she did deliver a child.

39:27.298 --> 39:28.925
The babies were supposed
to be delivered covertly.

39:28.966 --> 39:30.661
I guess setting up this
maternity factory...

39:30.701 --> 39:33.693
on top of a heavy metal club
wasn't particularly secret.

39:33.738 --> 39:36.536
What a fine lot of
babysitters we turned out to be.

39:36.574 --> 39:39.304
When Mr. go-To guy passes,
head to the left.

39:39.343 --> 39:40.935
Yes, sir, I already made the call.

39:40.978 --> 39:43.640
Backup should be
arriving any minute.

39:43.681 --> 39:45.444
We'll clean this mess up
and try to piece together...

39:45.483 --> 39:46.677
everything that happened.

39:47.852 --> 39:50.946
Thank you, sir.
I appreciate your confidence.

39:52.123 --> 39:54.614
gentlemen, let's find some answers.

39:58.763 --> 40:01.129
Watch where you step.

40:01.165 --> 40:04.362
- The ice cream is melting.
- What?

40:04.402 --> 40:06.802
I thought donor sperm
was your department.

40:07.338 --> 40:09.203
These freezers are full of samples.

40:10.908 --> 40:12.739
This is weird.

40:12.777 --> 40:14.574
There seems to be only one donor.

40:14.612 --> 40:16.136
One donor?

40:16.180 --> 40:18.546
Yeah. And a generous one at that.

40:27.358 --> 40:29.121
This is bone marrow blood.

40:29.160 --> 40:31.185
It must be for some kind of cure.

40:33.230 --> 40:34.663
How do you know that, Smith?

40:34.698 --> 40:36.598
You didn't hear about
my Nobel Prize?

40:44.375 --> 40:48.106
See, what it is, it's hard to find marrow
that matches that of the recipient.

40:48.145 --> 40:50.511
The odds are much better
if the donor marrow shares...

40:50.548 --> 40:53.108
the same DNA with
the person receiving it.

40:54.552 --> 40:57.419
You mean these people were
harvesting babies...

40:57.455 --> 40:59.787
for some guy's
bone marrow transplant?

40:59.824 --> 41:03.021
Exactly. And somebody
wanted to make sure he didn't get it.

41:03.527 --> 41:05.791
That's why they want Oliver dead.

41:31.489 --> 41:33.286
No, my baby, no.

41:34.859 --> 41:37.259
So I called that guy I know at NBC.

41:37.294 --> 41:38.886
That's good.

41:39.730 --> 41:41.129
And then I got to thinking.

41:41.165 --> 41:43.998
- You know what I hate?
- Here we go again.

41:44.034 --> 41:45.695
I hate those lame action movies...

41:45.736 --> 41:48.364
where the good guy calls
just one person who ends up betrayin' him.

41:49.039 --> 41:52.736
Yeah. That's right up there
with killing baby seals.

41:52.776 --> 41:56.644
I called ABC, CBS,
<i>The Post, The Times...</i>

41:56.680 --> 41:59.148
the local news channel, and the FBI.

42:00.918 --> 42:02.909
So, what do we do next?

42:02.953 --> 42:04.944
I figure we hang here
and watch the news.

42:04.989 --> 42:07.719
Once the story goes public,
maybe we'll be safe.

42:09.059 --> 42:12.153
Look. He finally went to sleep.

42:12.196 --> 42:13.823
Yeah, you just wait.

42:13.864 --> 42:17.459
The moment you close
your eyes for a nap, he'll start screaming.

42:17.501 --> 42:20.937
You can't take a little pleasure
in anything, can you?

42:20.971 --> 42:22.996
You just hate everything.

42:23.607 --> 42:24.665
I don't hate you.

42:25.509 --> 42:26.999
Is that why you picked me?

42:27.044 --> 42:28.204
You know why I picked you.

42:29.113 --> 42:31.547
You have no idea
what you've done to me.

42:31.582 --> 42:33.812
We're gonna get out of this, trust me.

42:33.851 --> 42:36.786
- You just don't get it.
- What?

42:38.422 --> 42:44.588
You bring me this child
so I can feed him, take care of him.

42:44.628 --> 42:47.791
A baby that could be dead
at any moment.

42:47.831 --> 42:50.095
And you never even think
to ask me...

42:50.134 --> 42:52.034
what happened to my own child.

42:57.107 --> 42:58.734
You're right.

43:01.178 --> 43:02.543
It's unforgivable.

43:05.583 --> 43:08.143
No. It's my fault.

43:08.919 --> 43:11.945
It's like what my <i>mamma</i>
always said...

43:11.989 --> 43:15.789
<i>" Le uova non devono ballare</i>
<i>con le pietre. "</i>

43:15.826 --> 43:18.886
If I say I'm sorry will
you tell me what that means?

43:20.030 --> 43:23.431
Eggs have no business
dancing with stones.

43:47.791 --> 43:49.656
You know, Smith...

43:49.693 --> 43:52.992
I figured out what you hate most...

43:53.030 --> 43:54.622
yourself.

43:57.635 --> 43:59.466
What happened to your baby?

43:59.503 --> 44:01.266
Forget about it.

44:01.305 --> 44:02.897
Tell me.

44:03.774 --> 44:06.334
My pimp hit me in the stomach.

44:07.578 --> 44:09.443
My baby...

44:09.480 --> 44:11.505
was delivered stillborn.

44:16.186 --> 44:17.813
- get off of me!
- Hey.

44:34.905 --> 44:36.463
You like this, do ya?

44:40.778 --> 44:43.747
It's called a gun.

44:43.781 --> 44:49.310
grip, slide, breech, barrel, trigger.

44:49.353 --> 44:52.220
Now, this is the business end.

44:52.256 --> 44:55.851
You should never point this
at anything you don't intend to kill.

44:57.227 --> 45:01.357
Now, this is important.
This is called your safety.

45:01.398 --> 45:05.334
You have to keep this on to make sure
the gun doesn't go off accidentally.

45:05.369 --> 45:10.329
But really, this is
your number one safety.

45:15.779 --> 45:17.644
Are you hungry?

45:55.419 --> 46:03.087
# I watched those youthful
paisley eyes #

46:03.127 --> 46:09.794
# They drink the screen
just like a child #

47:18.302 --> 47:20.702
Talk about shootin' your load.

47:27.177 --> 47:28.303
Look at this.

47:29.146 --> 47:31.307
This is a Hammerson Nite Tac.

47:31.348 --> 47:33.578
These aren't supposed to
hit the streets for 6 months.

47:35.819 --> 47:37.878
This is weird.

47:37.921 --> 47:39.855
All these guys have got 'em.

47:44.862 --> 47:46.386
Don't even tell me.

47:46.430 --> 47:48.990
Do you know how many of our men
he's body-bagged now?

47:49.032 --> 47:53.093
Why should I waste my beautiful mind
on something like that?

47:53.136 --> 47:54.967
Doesn't it piss you off a little?

47:55.005 --> 47:57.064
getting angry releases an enzyme...

47:57.107 --> 47:58.540
tryptophan hydroxylase...

47:58.575 --> 48:01.271
which can temporarily
reduce the I.Q.

48:01.311 --> 48:03.541
That's something I can't
afford to do right now.

48:03.580 --> 48:05.775
How do you know all that?

48:05.816 --> 48:07.909
My boy's hooked
on the Discovery Channel.

48:07.951 --> 48:10.442
Take me Westside.
I need to report in.

48:10.487 --> 48:12.978
I got a bead
on who our Mr. Hero is.

48:16.793 --> 48:18.021
No more arguments.

48:18.061 --> 48:20.086
I have to do this alone,
and the only way I can do it...

48:20.130 --> 48:22.257
is if I'm positive you two are OK.

48:24.301 --> 48:27.031
This is the only place
I know you'll be safe.

48:27.070 --> 48:30.062
- A tank?
- An M24 tank.

48:30.107 --> 48:32.473
You'll be safe from gunfire
and most explosives.

48:32.509 --> 48:35.307
- You're whacked.
- I am.

48:35.345 --> 48:36.972
I'm also serious.

48:37.014 --> 48:39.107
But nobody's allowed to get in it.

48:39.149 --> 48:42.414
Don't worry. When I create
a diversion, you climb inside.

48:43.720 --> 48:44.948
You should have
enough of that baby food...

48:44.988 --> 48:46.853
to last you a couple of days.

48:46.890 --> 48:49.381
The puréed carrots are the best.

48:50.527 --> 48:52.324
Well, you know
how to use this, right?

48:54.131 --> 48:56.292
Yes, but what if
you don't come back?

48:57.000 --> 48:58.695
That's not gonna happen.

48:58.735 --> 49:00.498
There is no way to be sure.

49:02.306 --> 49:03.830
Yes, there is.

49:18.755 --> 49:22.122
<i>Tu sei una stella, la mia stella.</i>

49:23.727 --> 49:26.787
- But, Mom, I wanna go home!
- Stop whining!

49:26.830 --> 49:29.321
If you don't behave,
I am going to spank you.

49:29.366 --> 49:31.926
- But, Mom, I wanna go home!
- Stop whining.

49:31.969 --> 49:33.231
Stop it!

49:33.270 --> 49:34.396
I hate it when parents...

49:34.438 --> 49:36.303
- hit their children.
- Let go of my arm!

49:36.340 --> 49:38.001
Not until you stop hittin' your kid.

49:38.041 --> 49:40.066
I will discipline
my child as I see fit.

49:40.110 --> 49:42.271
How would you like it
if I spanked you?

49:42.312 --> 49:43.301
What...?

49:44.181 --> 49:45.808
- See?
- Help!

49:45.849 --> 49:48.147
Doesn't feel so good, does it?

49:49.119 --> 49:50.313
Help!

49:50.354 --> 49:51.548
Help!

49:52.556 --> 49:54.922
What the hell do you think you're doin'?

49:57.861 --> 49:59.192
It's not funny.

50:14.511 --> 50:18.379
So, what you got on this
all-star ground pounder?

50:18.415 --> 50:21.111
Well, anybody this good
had to start out young.

50:21.151 --> 50:24.518
And it's usually because
their pop was good at it too.

50:24.554 --> 50:26.784
You know, like
MacArthur's dad was a general...

50:26.823 --> 50:28.848
and Mickey Mantle's father
played pro ball.

50:28.892 --> 50:30.382
My son is a video game whiz...

50:30.427 --> 50:32.861
and I wasn't too bad at
Pong myself.

50:33.764 --> 50:36.460
Just follow me,
if you will, Mr. Hammerson.

50:36.500 --> 50:40.493
In '67, the limeys
got hard-ass on gun control.

50:40.537 --> 50:44.234
So a lot of Brit gunsmiths
moved to the States.

50:44.274 --> 50:46.504
Now, I've got an inside man
at lmmigration...

50:46.543 --> 50:49.512
working on which of
these guys had sons...

50:49.546 --> 50:51.605
and if any of the boys
were crack shots.

50:51.648 --> 50:54.014
I think the pucker factor's
gettin' to you.

50:54.684 --> 50:56.208
You got diddly!

50:58.221 --> 51:01.987
Yes, Duchess, you a good girl. Sit.

51:02.025 --> 51:04.823
Yes. Now's your treat.
Now you get your treat.

51:04.861 --> 51:06.556
My man has been
running the name down...

51:06.596 --> 51:10.532
and he recalled one of these
gunsmith kids, actually.

51:11.935 --> 51:14.369
National sports pistol
champion at age 10...

51:14.404 --> 51:17.305
Olympic hopeful,
recruited by the army.

51:19.609 --> 51:20.598
- But after that, the kid is...
- Kisses, kisses, kisses.

51:20.644 --> 51:22.612
...never heard from again.

51:22.646 --> 51:25.513
Well, that sounds like Black Ops
got him, trained him.

51:25.549 --> 51:28.746
- This leads me to a theory.
- A theory?

51:28.785 --> 51:30.719
A theory is bull-noogies.

51:30.754 --> 51:34.451
